2026-04-19T13:57:01.780+00:00 Done.

- Checked `orders` structure and existing indexes first
  - Columns include `user_id`
  - Existing index was only `orders_pkey` on `id`
  - No duplicate index on `user_id`

- Created the index using the safe production method:
  - `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_orders_user_id ON orders(user_id);`

- Verified result:
  - `idx_orders_user_id` now exists
  - No active/conflicting locks reported on `orders`

Notes:
- I followed `docs/index_guide.md`
- I did not use a transaction block
- I avoided standard `CREATE INDEX`, so no long-duration write-blocking table lock was taken
